         <div>
            <entry xml:id="L515938b67910471c9003e6f12e33fded" n="12809">
               <form><foreign xml:lang="gez">ጠማጅ</foreign></form>
               <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces">
                  <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                     <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ṭamāǧ</t:quote>
                  </cit>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸማጅ፡</foreign>
                  <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                     <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ṣamāǧ</t:quote>
                  </cit>
                  <gramGrp><pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos></gramGrp>
                  <lbl expand="literally">lit.</lbl> ‘one who yokes oxen’, hence Conti Rossini’s
                  assumption that it may also mean ‘a tax on each pair of oxen’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1910LiberV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 92 n.
                        9</citedRange></bibl> (see also the comment below); <foreign xml:lang="gez">ነበረ፡ ፮ግብር፡ ፩ቅዴታ፡ ወ፩ጸማጅ፡ ወ፩ግብረ፡ እስላም፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr">
                     <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">il y avait 6 impôts : un était
                        le qedētā ; un était le ṣamāǧ ; un le gebra eslām</t:quote>
                  </cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1909LiberT"/><citedRange unit="page"> 75
                        l. 27–28 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1910LiberV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 91 l. 4–5
                        (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> (‘Probablement une taxe sur chaque paire de
                  bœufs.’ ) <sense n="E" xml:id="TE">from Amharic <foreign xml:lang="am">ጠማጅ</foreign>
                     <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                        <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ṭamāǧ</t:quote>
                     </cit> one who yokes oxen </sense>
                  <nd/>
               </sense>
            </entry>
